        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:23PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 1223 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marcellus, or 12 miles northwest of Three Rivers, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, Marcellus, Colon, Flowerfield, Leonidas, Mendon, Moore
Park, Howardsville, Wasepi, Fishers Lake, Fairfax, and Wakelee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
